      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUC81d14f402b7410058c2787d9909970d2"></a>Rear suspension system
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7646"> </a>The rear suspension system uses a hydraulic single shock absorber (1) adjustable for rebound and spring preload.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7648"> </a>Shock absorber pivots onto a swinging arm at the bottom and rear subframe at the top. This system makes the motorcycle extremely
            stable.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7650"> </a>For rear shock absorber adjustment, refer to Section "<a href="77285.html#DUC1198eba02a5e10058d51d82abd9709d2">Adjusting the rear shock absorber</a>" for the base version or Section "<a href="77776.html#DUCa414a5502a5e10058d55d82abd9709d2"> Adjusting the rear shock absorber</a>" for the Pikes Peak, Granturismo or Touring versions.
         </div>
      </div>
